          %h2 Home Based vs. Brick & Mortar
          %p There are differences between starting a Home Based Business and a Brick and Mortar. For example, if you’re starting a restaurant you may need a liquor license, zoning inspection, etc.

          %h3 Brick & Mortar
          %p There are a lot of things to take into account before signing the lease. Consider the following as you select a location for your business:

          %h3 Zoning:
          %p Different business types are only allowed in certain parts of the city, and it is illegal to run a business in a building that is not permitted or zoned for that type of activity. Always check with the City’s planning department (link) before signing a lease.

          {{ cms:partial:shared/link_box:"http://www.gatewaycogsiteprospector.org/search.html?zpesst=gatewaycog&zpemode=search&zpesearchtype=BUILDINGS&zpeminsize=1100&zpemaxsize=14000&zpeattributes=145%3A%5B%3D%5D1&zpepropertytype=9&zpegeoentitylist=%2B":"EXPLORE":"Free commercial property search tool" }}

          %p Contact the Planning and Zoning departments to confirm that your business type works in that zoned area.

